    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nWhen using a function parameter as an exponent the type is not correctly inferred even if it is statically typed.\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\nCode:\r\n```cython\r\ncdef main(int n):\r\n  cdef int iterations = 2**n\r\n  for _ in range(iterations):\r\n    ...\r\n```\r\n\r\nCompiler Output:\r\n```\r\ncdef main(int n):\r\n    cdef int iterations = 2**n\r\n                           ^\r\n------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nbinary_trees.pyx:17:27: Cannot assign type 'double' to 'int'\r\n```\r\n\r\nFix:\r\n```cython\r\ncdef main(int n):\r\n  cdef int iterations = int(2**n)\r\n  for _ in range(iterations):\r\n    ...\r\n```\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nIt should not be necessary to add the int() cast\n\n### OS\n\nLinux\n\n### Python version\n\n3.11\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.0.2\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": "2023-09-20T18:35:02Z",
