            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The is working as intended (and a breaking change in Cython 3). If `n` is negative then the result won't be integer, therefore the result can't be integer.\r\n\r\nYou can restore the old behaviour using the `cpow` directive (https://cython.readthedocs.io/en/latest/src/userguide/source_files_and_compilation.html#compiler-directives).\r\n\r\nI think we were a bit cleverer about guessing user intent with double**double exponents (which now become complex) - in this case we'd assume you wanted the old behaviour because of what you assigned it to. In hindsight we possibly should have done the same for `int`, but I don't think we want to go back and start adding new cases - it's complicated enough already.",
